<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Server</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: Ones where the &quot;Sleeper&quot; is &quot;Awake&quot;<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Items</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: SoD/Gnome Mask<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Problem</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: Neither can be attained now that the Sleeper on that particular server has been set free. Both items are dropable. So items can be farmed on a Legends server, considering that the Sleeper has not yet been woken up. The items can then find their way back to a server where the Sleeper IS awake.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Example1</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: a_RichDude_01 sets up an exchange with a_UberFarmingGroup_01 to get his SoDless Warrior a SoD. He transfers, gets his SoD (and anything else he might have set up arrangements for) then returns back to his original server, because his guild and friends are still there.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Example2</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: a_2ndTierUberGuild_871387913879123 transfers enough people from their guild to Legends. They farm what they need from the Warders and transfers back to distribute the wealth accordingly.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Server</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: Friona Vie<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Items</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: Kunark BP/Legs and other dropables equivalent of value or more<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Problem</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: Friona Vie is a new (non-split) server. Even though their top guild (Fire and Fury) are at PoG lvl now, that still leaves a rather decent if not large gap on other guilds. Dropable items that are largely trivial to obtain for older servers are still obstacles for a majority of FV.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Example</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: a_RichDude_02 sets up an exchange with a_OverstockedGuild_01 to get his guild set up on Kunark BPs and Legs. He transfers, gets the gear (and anything else he might have set up arrangements for) then returns back to FV to distribute the wealth accordingly.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> NOTE</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: This would also assume that there might be people on FV with this kind of gumption that even exist.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Server</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: Friona Vie<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Items</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: Anything that's usually no drop<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Problem</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: Items are all dropable on FV. I assume this also goes for quest items and quest rewards; such as sov armor and epics. <br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Example</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: a_UberFarmingGroup_02 gathers a bunch of various &quot;no drop” loots and transfers some players to Legends to equip Legends players whom would never &quot;see the end game&quot; for a nice fee and cover charge.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> NOTE</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: IMHO, it shouldn't be much of a problem at all though. Considering FV is a new server, they'll need all that gear for a while still. So by the time they have a decent number of guilds at ST/Ssra/NToV/etc lvl, I would suppose there wouldn't be much of a way to do this considering there is a server limit for Legends. This would also assume that there might be people on FV with this kind of gumption that even exist.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> FACT</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: When people have lots of money, things that would seem much to expensive to a lot of us would look like pocket change to them.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> FACT</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: If people can make a decent profit at something that requires little work, there will be people willing to do it!<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> FACT</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: There ARE people with money (and people who said if they had the money) who've said they WOULD do these &quot;examples&quot; if they were given the opportunity. You really think I thought all this stuff up by myself? ;p<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> FACT</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: VI doesn't want a flood of items to enter the world. YET, they have opened the door of opportunity for servers to flood in items they shouldn't have yet or any more of!<br>
<br>
Will it happen? No idea, but the fact still remains the same. IT COULD VERY WELL HAPPEN! =) Also, my apologies to FV for pointing you guys out as an example. I am not saying you would do this, but saying there IS a possibility it could happen if you do have some unsavory individuals now or in the future.<br>
<br>
Oh, here's another possibility to Legends in general...<br>
<br>
Maybe it's an experiment to see how many people will pay for an online game? If it works out well, maybe the future price of EQ will get jacked up a bit.<br>
<br>
